COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. Pauline MUELLER. No. 5222. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. April 13, 1934. . Prank J. Wideman, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. George K. Bowden, of Chicago, Ill., for respondent.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and FITZ-HENRY, Cireuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for petitioner, counsel for respondent consenting thereto, it is now here ordered and adjudged that this cause bo docketed in this court and that the petition for a review of the decision of the United States Board of Tax Appeals entered on October 4, 1933, be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
